<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4544432>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 9. Nephochaetopteryx cyaneiventris Lopes, 1936, male terminalia. Specimen from Petrópolis, Rio de Janeiro (MZUSP). A. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view; arrow showing rounded dorsal projection. B. Cerci, dorsal view (spines and setation omitted on the left side). C. Pregonite, left lateral view. D. Postgonite, left lateral view. E. Sternite 5, ventral view (setation omitted on the left side). F. Phallus, lateral view. Abbreviations: bp = basiphallus; dp = distiphallus; ip = inner process of vesica; ls = lateral stylus; ms = median stylus; ve = vesica. Scale bars: A, B, E = 0.1 mm; C, D, F = 0.05 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4544432/files/figure.png" .

